      <p>Furthermore, the KRAS-G13D mutant seems to be less expressed in HKE3 compared to HCT116. In order to quantify the levels of KRAS transcripts in HCT116 and HKE3, differential expression analysis for the two cell lines was performed. A fold change of 1.89 (FDR = 0.006) shows that the KRAS gene is less expressed in HKE3 than in HCT116. An isoform expression analysis using Kallisto [<xref rid="pone.0171435.ref026" ref-type="bibr">26</xref>] show that it is a single KRAS isoform (ENST00000311936) out of four known that differ in expression level between these cell lines (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="pone.0171435.g005">Fig 5A</xref>).</p>
